Claim Before Competitors

The internet still has frontiers.

Not because topics don’t exist.

Because good maps don’t exist.

The first coherent, useful map often becomes the reference point.

Wikipedia claimed encyclopedic summaries.

GitHub claimed collaborative code hosting.

Stack Overflow claimed practical programming Q&A.

None of them owned those subjects—they became the places people naturally went because they were consistently useful.

